705083f-a.title: Brooklyn: Jamaica Avenue - Fanchon Place
705083f-a.text:
Jamaica Ave., at the N.E. corner of Fanohon Place, showing Tubbs
Rotel (later in the 1870's it was known as Chris. Koch's Hotel, after many
years, it became known as Cavaluzso's Cafe. It was demolished in 1929).
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
